id: agents/contributor-architecture
title: "contributor architecture disclosure"
kind: agent-template
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-01

purpose: >
  Give AI-assisted contributors a simple way to show how their agent helps the
  project.

fields:
  mission: "what should the agent help with"
  model_or_tooling: "what AI, prompts, scripts, or services are used"
  reads: "what files, issues, pages, or records it reads"
  writes: "what it can change or propose"
  proof: "how humans verify the output"
  boundaries: "what it cannot do without approval"
  replay: "what changed after using it"

use:
  Fill this out when proposing an AI-agent contributor workflow.

proof:
  source:
    - agents/contributor-agent.yawn
    - .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/ai-agent-contributor.yml
  status: seed-backed
